t the use-case: I encountered the issue when I tried to enable compile-time checks for logging in our company, where we already have many messages in code. Changing them to indexed would not practical, nor very nice to the user of such API. The named argument is used to log \"strerror\", similarly as was common with printf, i.e. original `%m` is replaced by fmt `{m}`. This is achieved by adding a named argument `\"m\"_a` as the last argument after what user provides in a log function. I also have a similar implementation [in open-source here](https://github.com/rbrich/xcikit/blob/eaab9305ef61d23d88bdb43a6292c964df6ad3ff/src/xci/core/log.h#L65).\r\n\r\nIt would be nice if such a logging function could have the format checked in compile-time, but I understand that the named argument support is still somewhat experimental.","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/fmtlib/fmt/issues/comments/1253663042/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"rbrich","id":6216152,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjYyMTYxNTI=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/6216152?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/rbrich","html_url":"https://github.com/rbrich","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rbrich/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rbrich/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rbrich/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rbrich/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rbrich/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rbrich/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rbrich/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rbrich/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rbrich/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":