in":false,"push":false,"triage":false,"pull":true}},"pull_request":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/fmtlib/fmt/pulls/3214","html_url":"https://github.com/fmtlib/fmt/pull/3214","diff_url":"https://github.com/fmtlib/fmt/pull/3214.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/fmtlib/fmt/pull/3214.patch","merged_at":"2022-12-04T16:13:26Z"},"body":"Fixes #3105\r\n\r\nLooks like this is enough to fix the issue.\r\n\r\nI compared the runtime checking with compile-time checking and adjusted the compile-time version to mirror the runtime one.\r\n\r\nThe runtime check is this (second function for named args):\r\n```\r\n    FMT_CONSTEXPR auto on_arg_id(int id) -> int {\r\n      return parse_context.check_arg_id(id), id;\r\n    }\r\n    FMT_CONSTEXPR auto on_arg_id(basic_string_view<Char> id) -> int {\r\n      int arg_id = context.arg_id(id);\r\n      if (arg_id < 0) on_error(\"argument not found\");\r\n      return arg_id;\r\n    }\r\n```\r\nIt returns the arg index directly without running it through the `check_arg_id`, unlike the indexed arg check.\r\n\r\n<!--\r\nPlease read the contribution guidelines before submitting a pull request:\r\nhttps://github.com/fmtlib/fmt/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md.\r\nBy submitting this pull request, you agree that your contributions are licensed\r\nunder the {fmt} license, and agree to future changes to the licensing.\r\n-->\r\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/fmtlib/fmt/issues/3214/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/fmtlib/fmt/issues/3214/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}},"event":"cross-referenced"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/fmtlib/fmt/issues/comments/1332156747","html_url":"https://github.com/fmtlib/fmt/issues/3105#issuecomment-1332156747","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/fmtlib/fmt/issues/3105","id":1332156747,"node_id":"IC_kwDOAGurSs5PZxlL","user":{"login":"rbri